<br>
Ok, i see your point on the sign up and alliance thing, but when i see a member of a guild doing Nagafen in Nexus asking random people if they would like to join, and I've been sent tells Personally asking if me or my guild would like to help, that is NOT an alliance thing, it is a public raid.  There are alliances involved, such as TI and SL allying for kills, but if there are 5 guilds involved, it's not quite the alliance thing anymore.  I see people in the zone, and in Lavastorm, and in Nexus and PoK being asked simply because they are lvl 45-52 if they would like to join a dragon raid for the &quot;Chance to roll on phat lewtz&quot;.  If it was strictly a few guilds and maybe a couple of guests, that's ok, but this random asking Joe off of the Street thing is getting out of hand.  Next thing you know a guild with 3 people the right lvl is gonna be signing up and asking 35 people they hardly or outright don't know to join in so they can have a shot at killing him.  These public raids fail, and fail, and fail, and do nothign but waste time for the Few guilds that actually take time to prepare and think this stuff thru, and get the kills quick and clean.<br>
<br>
I'm not pointing fingers here, but I will ask that the guilds, in respect to the Few of us that Can and DO take out these dragons, try to keep it to a limited number of guests.  I'm getting tired Personally of being sent tells by X Friend #1 askin me if I want to join a Dragon raid being hosted by X Guild(s), and if I have any friends that want to, invite them to.  It's classic Public raids on Schedule Dragons.  If we want to make them public raidable, and say Screw the schedule, we could do that, but it would be a HUGE pain in the ass of Prachlyn And the guilds trying to Successfully raid him(them).<br>
<br>
I refer to Nagafen throughout my posts because, to date, he is the only one being contested.  FoV has taken Vox every time she has spawned and no other guild has even tried to lay claim to her as of yet.  If anyone feels like taking a shot, we welcome it, but until someone can successfully take out Nagafen, their shot at Vox will pretty much be nothing more than a long CR.<br>
<br>
This is all my opinions, i still wish for more Feedback from Guild leaders, and Prach's opinion of course.  Keep me updated as well guys, I don't want my guild flamed for taking a dragon on our turn when other guilds don't post their Fails/Success's.  I have had to work my way all the way to Nagafen twice now just to find out if he's up, and the trip out is just as bad if not worse.<br>
<br>
Respectfully, <br>
<br>
Reptylle Bloodscayle<br>
Disciple of the 52 Scale<br>
Proud Officer of Fellowship of Vindication<br>
Public Relations Dept<br>
