<br>
Hello all, I have been lurking in this forum for many a years (before Tanje took over) and I hope that I can provide some background on the aspect of alliances (at least how it used to be handled).  Back when this was formed, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>believe</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (and please do not kill me for my memory is not as good as it used to be <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) that the guild that signed up to kill the dragon needed to field approx.  80% of the raid force going up against Naggy / Vox.  If they couldn't do that and they needed to call onto other guilds, that it would constitute an alliance between guild.<br>
<br>
Case in point, back when I was in Ravens Wings and we were actively signing up for Naggy, we had close ties with CoP and we would invite them to tag alone with us.  They would return the favor and extend the invitation to us when they were up.  Both of us were able to field 80% of the raid so we continued to sign up as separate entities.  When our numbers fell and we couldn't field the required numbers, we then started signing up on the schedule as one force &quot;The Alliance&quot;.<br>
<br>
I do not wish to pick a side on this matter, I just wanted to lend some history on how Alliances were handled.  Oh, I also believe that when guilds entered into an Alliance, they actually had to state (to the board) what the Alliance's name was and what guilds were in them. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=529000"> Taug Inator</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Level 64 Dwarf Warlord of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com">Vis Veres</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Master Baker, Pottery and Drunk</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
